WEBVTT

00:02.403 --> 00:04.972
**

00:05.005 --> 00:07.041
Hey!
It says, "Don't walk."

00:08.542 --> 00:10.644
Dude, there are
zero cars coming.

00:10.678 --> 00:13.514
Yeah, but your safety
is my responsibility.

00:14.448 --> 00:16.850
I'm the newest member
of the Safety Patrol.

00:16.884 --> 00:19.587
I'd say, "Congrats,"
but I don't really mean it.

00:19.620 --> 00:20.754
I'll take it anyway.

00:20.788 --> 00:23.023
Just so you know,
next time you break a rule,

00:23.057 --> 00:24.725
I'll be forced
to write you up.

00:24.758 --> 00:28.096
**

00:29.530 --> 00:32.233
How does the vest look
from the back?

00:32.266 --> 00:35.069
**

00:35.103 --> 00:37.438
-- Captions by VITAC --

00:37.471 --> 00:38.606
* Fresh off the boat

00:38.639 --> 00:40.341
* I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go *

00:40.374 --> 00:42.610
* If you don't know, homey,
now you know *

00:42.643 --> 00:43.911
* Fresh off the boat

00:43.944 --> 00:46.247
* Homey, you don't know
where I come from *

00:46.280 --> 00:47.715
* But I know where I'm goin'

00:47.748 --> 00:50.518
* I'm fresh off the boat

00:50.551 --> 00:53.521
[ Indistinct conversations ]

00:53.554 --> 00:55.556
I can't believe
that guy.

00:55.589 --> 00:56.557
What guy? Schwimmer?

00:56.590 --> 00:57.558
No. Trent.

00:57.591 --> 00:59.227
He's on
the Safety Patrol.

00:59.260 --> 01:01.295
Why would he do something
so lame?

01:01.329 --> 01:03.063
I know. I told him
he should do something cool

01:03.097 --> 01:04.465
and join cheerleading
like me.

01:04.498 --> 01:06.300
You're a cheerleader?

01:06.334 --> 01:09.603
Yep -- The first male
top of pyramid in 30 years.

01:12.140 --> 01:13.774
What glass ceiling?

01:13.807 --> 01:15.976
We've all joined
school clubs.

01:16.009 --> 01:17.278
We told you this.

01:17.311 --> 01:18.812
Yeah,
and I told you --

01:18.846 --> 01:21.081
when it's important,
repeat yourself.

01:21.115 --> 01:23.884
Okay -- I'm playing the lead
in the school musical.

01:23.917 --> 01:25.986
We couldn't get the rights
to "Rent,"

01:26.019 --> 01:28.289
so we're doing our own version,
"Brent."

01:28.322 --> 01:30.891
I play the evil landlord,
Brent.

01:30.924 --> 01:33.060
It's pretty much
the same show,

01:33.093 --> 01:35.496
only instead of AIDS,
everyone has the flu.

01:35.529 --> 01:37.431
Walter, are you hearing
this nonsense?

01:37.465 --> 01:40.834
The dog knew --
She knew she was dying.

01:40.868 --> 01:43.237
Yo, life?
She's intense.

01:43.271 --> 01:44.772
[ Exhales sharply ]

01:44.805 --> 01:46.307
Are you reading
for fun?

01:46.340 --> 01:47.775
Yeah.
I joined the book club.

01:47.808 --> 01:49.343
Every month
is a different theme.

01:49.377 --> 01:51.078
This month is healing.

01:51.111 --> 01:52.280
What is happening?

01:52.313 --> 01:54.448
Am I the only person
who cares about our reputation?

01:54.482 --> 01:56.450
You guys are making us
look like losers.

01:56.484 --> 01:58.286
We don't
look like losers.

01:58.319 --> 02:01.589
**

02:01.622 --> 02:02.956
Sorry.

02:02.990 --> 02:05.659
* Don't worry about it

02:06.894 --> 02:09.062
[ Light laughter ]

02:10.030 --> 02:11.265
Why would you sing,
Dave?

02:11.299 --> 02:12.966
Now the Sackers
think we're lame.

02:13.000 --> 02:15.035
I mean, they're not as cool
as the jocks,

02:15.068 --> 02:16.570
but they're cooler
than the dip kids.

02:18.071 --> 02:20.208
Life's too short to worry,
Eddie.

02:20.241 --> 02:22.543
You never know
when the flu could strike.

02:22.576 --> 02:24.345
That's the message
of "Brent."

02:24.378 --> 02:27.181
**

02:27.215 --> 02:28.616
[ Doorbell rings ]

02:28.649 --> 02:29.683
[ Sighs ]

02:30.718 --> 02:34.222
Can a child get that,
please?

02:35.256 --> 02:37.625
Where's my
favorite author?

02:37.658 --> 02:39.627
I don't know
where Mary Higgins Clark lives.

02:39.660 --> 02:41.295
Dallas?
Probably Dallas.

02:41.329 --> 02:42.630
I was talking
about you.

02:42.663 --> 02:43.997
[ Scoffs ]
How's the book going?

02:44.031 --> 02:44.998
Intense.

02:45.032 --> 02:46.534
I have all these
publisher notes.

02:46.567 --> 02:48.035
I keep having to
get on the phone

02:48.068 --> 02:51.739
with people who have names
like "Vera" and "Terry."

02:51.772 --> 02:52.906
And on top of that,

02:52.940 --> 02:55.676
I have to take an author photo
for the book jacket.

02:55.709 --> 02:57.545
Oh, that's exciting!

02:57.578 --> 02:59.380
I'll give you the name
of the woman

02:59.413 --> 03:01.148
who did
Marvin's business cards.

03:01.181 --> 03:03.150
She is
super expensive.

03:03.183 --> 03:05.986
I'm not spending money
on a picture. I'll just
have you take it.

03:06.019 --> 03:07.321
I would love to.

03:07.355 --> 03:10.524
As a former makeup artist
for the hit musical "Cats,"

03:10.558 --> 03:12.560
I'll make sure
you look your best.

03:13.594 --> 03:15.162
Don't make
me look like a cat.

03:15.195 --> 03:17.231
There's nothing scarier
than a cat person.

03:17.265 --> 03:18.866
Mm, disagree.

03:18.899 --> 03:21.269
You ever see someone
make chorizo?

03:21.302 --> 03:22.736
**

03:22.770 --> 03:24.438
[ Bell rings ]

03:24.472 --> 03:26.240
Hey, bud.

03:26.274 --> 03:28.542
Sorry if I came off
as harsh yesterday --

03:28.576 --> 03:30.043
still trying
to find the right balance

03:30.077 --> 03:31.412
of authority
and warmth.

03:31.445 --> 03:33.381
It's okay.
That being said,

03:33.414 --> 03:35.449
I'm gonna have to ask you
to change your shoes.

03:35.483 --> 03:37.217
Why?
Dress-code violation.

03:37.251 --> 03:39.287
You know this is
a closed-toed campus.

03:39.320 --> 03:40.588
I'm not changing.

03:40.621 --> 03:42.956
These slides make me look like
a relaxed athlete.

03:42.990 --> 03:44.925
Really hoped
it wouldn't come to this.

03:44.958 --> 03:47.127
I'm gonna need a signature
from your mom or dad

03:47.160 --> 03:49.096
or whatever legal guardian
you live with.

03:49.129 --> 03:50.864
[ Paper rustles ]
Trent, you know
my mom and dad.

03:50.898 --> 03:53.601
And do us both a favor --
don't forge.

03:53.634 --> 03:55.202
I have access
to all parent signatures

03:55.235 --> 03:56.704
in the
principal's office,

03:56.737 --> 03:59.139
and I can spot a trace job
a mile away.

03:59.172 --> 04:02.109
I appraised my sister's
promise ring with this.

04:02.142 --> 04:04.545
[ Sighs ]

04:04.578 --> 04:06.113
**

04:06.146 --> 04:09.717
On a scale of 1 to 10,
how likely am I to recommend?

04:09.750 --> 04:11.452
I'd say a 6.

04:11.485 --> 04:14.221
How often do I talk
to my friends about baking soda?

04:14.254 --> 04:15.456
Never.

04:15.489 --> 04:16.790
If anyone answered anything
other than "Never,"

04:16.824 --> 04:17.791
I'd be shocked.

04:17.825 --> 04:18.992
[ Door creaks ]

04:19.026 --> 04:21.329
Three people said,
"All the time"?

04:21.362 --> 04:23.130
Why are you sharing
this information with me?

04:23.163 --> 04:25.466
I thought this survey
was confidential.

04:25.499 --> 04:27.401
No, don't tell me
their names!

04:27.435 --> 04:30.003
Sorry, Eddie.
What's up?

04:30.037 --> 04:31.605
Your boy got busted.

04:31.639 --> 04:33.073
Eddie!

04:33.106 --> 04:34.975
[ Laughs ]

04:35.008 --> 04:36.444
Dress-code violation?

04:36.477 --> 04:38.612
For a second, I thought you
actually did something wrong.

04:38.646 --> 04:40.113
I did
do something wrong.

04:40.147 --> 04:41.982
These slides
are against the rules.

04:42.015 --> 04:43.951
Anything could have happened
to my toes -- anything.

04:43.984 --> 04:45.453
Okay, okay.

04:45.486 --> 04:47.955
I'm just relieved you didn't
commit some bigger offense.

04:47.988 --> 04:49.289
I knew
you were a good boy.

04:49.323 --> 04:50.858
Don't call me that.

04:50.891 --> 04:51.959
It's a compliment.

04:51.992 --> 04:53.193
When I look at you
and your friends,

04:53.226 --> 04:55.329
I see a group
of really good boys.

04:55.363 --> 04:57.130
**

04:57.164 --> 04:58.866
[ "COPS" theme song plays ]

04:58.899 --> 05:02.370
* Good boys, whatcha want,
whatcha want *

05:02.403 --> 05:04.472
* Whatcha gonna do?

05:04.505 --> 05:07.375
* When these boys
are friends with you? *

05:07.408 --> 05:08.876
* Good boys, good boys

05:08.909 --> 05:10.544
* Whatcha gonna do?

05:10.578 --> 05:12.846
* Whatcha gonna do when
they're friends with you? *

05:12.880 --> 05:13.981
* Good boys, good boys
Eddie!

05:14.014 --> 05:15.549
Hey, let me
ask you something.

05:15.583 --> 05:18.318
How often do you talk to
your friends about baking soda?

05:19.587 --> 05:21.455
**

05:21.489 --> 05:22.623
Those guys
are jerks, Dave.

05:22.656 --> 05:23.857
Don't let them
steal your smile.

05:23.891 --> 05:24.958
They're just thugs.

05:24.992 --> 05:26.860
What's going on?
Is someone bullying Dave?

05:26.894 --> 05:28.796
Yeah,
the producers of "Rent."

05:28.829 --> 05:30.664
Trent wrote to them
about our show --

05:30.698 --> 05:32.833
said it was his
Safety Patrol responsibility

05:32.866 --> 05:34.234
to put it
on their radar.

05:34.267 --> 05:35.636
Now they're trying
to stop it --

05:35.669 --> 05:38.338
something about a blatant
disregard of copyright law.

05:38.372 --> 05:41.074
Trent's out of control, and he's
taking us down with him.

05:41.108 --> 05:43.544
We have to show him
and the rest of these doubters

05:43.577 --> 05:45.245
that we don't play
by his rules.

05:45.278 --> 05:46.547
What are we gonna do?

05:46.580 --> 05:48.048
I'll tell you
what we're gonna do --

05:48.081 --> 05:50.651
tomorrow,
we all wear slides to school.

05:50.684 --> 05:52.486
**

05:52.520 --> 05:54.622
This is happening!

05:59.893 --> 06:03.731
Okay, so this will just be
a free flow of ideas.

06:03.764 --> 06:05.566
We'll see
where inspiration leads,

06:05.599 --> 06:07.601
we'll let the author photo
come to us.

06:08.636 --> 06:10.337
[ Sighs ]
I'm ready.

06:10.370 --> 06:12.773
* She's going the distance

06:12.806 --> 06:15.576
* She's going for speed

06:15.609 --> 06:16.777
* She's all alone

06:16.810 --> 06:18.011
* All alone

06:18.045 --> 06:20.948
* All alone
in her time of need *

06:20.981 --> 06:22.082
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

06:22.115 --> 06:24.518
* She's going the distance

06:24.552 --> 06:26.787
* She's going for speed

06:30.824 --> 06:32.359
[ Chatter ]

06:32.392 --> 06:35.896
**

06:35.929 --> 06:38.065
[ Sighs ]
Eddie, Eddie, Eddie...

06:38.098 --> 06:40.267
Whatcha gonna do, Red,
write us all up?

06:40.300 --> 06:43.303
What do you mean?
Come on, guys,
show the man your feet.

06:50.444 --> 06:51.645
What the hell?
Sorry, man.

06:51.679 --> 06:53.981
If we get in trouble, we can't
do our school activities.

06:54.014 --> 06:56.817
If I get detention,
I'll have to miss rehearsal,

06:56.850 --> 06:58.385
and if
I miss rehearsal,

06:58.418 --> 07:00.454
my understudy
gets my part.

07:02.590 --> 07:04.725
Hey, Eli.

07:04.758 --> 07:07.427
He's mediocre at best.

07:07.461 --> 07:09.930
Sorry, Eddie.
I guess we are good boys.

07:11.765 --> 07:13.433
[ Dramatic music plays ]

07:13.467 --> 07:15.068
Saturday Detention?

07:15.102 --> 07:16.570
At least
you'll still have Sunday free

07:16.604 --> 07:18.672
to cheer on the Dolphins
and pray for your soul.

07:18.706 --> 07:23.511
**

07:28.048 --> 07:29.583
Weird to be at school
on a Saturday.

07:29.617 --> 07:30.851
Do you think
they still

07:30.884 --> 07:32.452
have the vending machines
plugged in?

07:32.486 --> 07:34.522
[ Chuckles ] If you had stopped
wearing open-toed shoes

07:34.555 --> 07:35.989
when you were warned,
you wouldn't be here.

07:36.023 --> 07:37.491
I'm not telling your mom
about this.

07:37.525 --> 07:39.426
She's stressed enough
about her book as it is.

07:39.459 --> 07:41.862
Well, I better get in there
with the other delinquents.

07:41.895 --> 07:43.931
You know why guys like you
knock everything?

07:43.964 --> 07:45.298
It's because
you're afraid.

07:45.332 --> 07:46.466
Who said I was afraid?

07:46.500 --> 07:48.502
It's a quote
from "The Breakfast Club" --

07:48.536 --> 07:50.604
first American movie
I fell in love with.

07:50.638 --> 07:53.273
The first movie I fell in love
with was "A Goofy Movie."

07:53.306 --> 07:55.042
Broke my heart
when Goofy found out

07:55.075 --> 07:56.677
his son was embarrassed
by him.

07:56.710 --> 07:58.478
**

07:58.512 --> 08:02.282
[ Indistinct whispering ]

08:02.315 --> 08:03.884
[ Door slams ]

08:03.917 --> 08:05.519
[ Sighs ]

08:05.553 --> 08:09.256
**

08:10.591 --> 08:12.292
So, what are you
in for?

08:12.325 --> 08:14.895
Wearing slides.
Twice.

08:14.928 --> 08:17.230
We got busted
for sacking.

08:17.264 --> 08:18.899
They took our hacky sacks
and everything.

08:18.932 --> 08:21.301
Like, when did hacky sacks
ever hurt anybody?

08:21.334 --> 08:23.370
All right, listen up,
buttholes.

08:23.403 --> 08:26.139
Personally, I'd rather be
anywhere else on a Saturday,

08:26.173 --> 08:29.142
but my timeshare in Tallahassee
isn't gonna pay for itself.

08:29.176 --> 08:31.344
Here are the rules --
no eating.

08:31.378 --> 08:32.646
But you're eating.

08:32.680 --> 08:34.582
Run laps.
But this is detention.

08:34.615 --> 08:36.917
What did I say?!
[ Sighs ]

08:36.950 --> 08:40.020
No eating, no talking,
no sleeping.

08:40.053 --> 08:41.755
Okay, that's it.

08:41.789 --> 08:45.593
**

08:45.626 --> 08:46.860
Yep.

08:46.894 --> 08:49.897
**

08:53.767 --> 08:56.236
All right, w-what do you
think? Should we each
pick 10 favorites?

08:56.269 --> 08:58.271
You can.
I hate them all.

08:58.305 --> 09:00.741
What?
Jessica, these are great.

09:00.774 --> 09:02.042
My smile is off.

09:02.075 --> 09:03.711
It doesn't exude
the quiet confidence

09:03.744 --> 09:05.613
of a Stephen King
or a Danielle Steel.

09:05.646 --> 09:07.114
What about this one?

09:07.147 --> 09:08.515
No, here.
Yes.

09:08.548 --> 09:09.950
The one where you're peeking out
from the closet.

09:09.983 --> 09:11.451
You look so pretty.

09:11.484 --> 09:13.286
Well, of course I look pretty.
That's a given,

09:13.320 --> 09:14.855
but none of these
are good enough.

09:14.888 --> 09:16.624
I'm just gonna have to use
this old picture.

09:16.657 --> 09:18.191
Now, tell me
that picture doesn't scream

09:18.225 --> 09:20.127
"professional author."

09:20.160 --> 09:23.430
It does scream
"professional author"...

09:23.463 --> 09:24.765
because this is
Amy Tan.

09:24.798 --> 09:25.866
[ Sighs ]
I know.

09:25.899 --> 09:27.267
I thought
my publisher might go,

09:27.300 --> 09:29.202
"Oh, this looks
a lot like Amy Tan,"

09:29.236 --> 09:31.605
but then be too nervous
to say anything.

09:31.639 --> 09:32.940
Evan:
[ Clears throat ]

09:32.973 --> 09:35.308
Respectfully, if it didn't
work out with Honey,

09:35.342 --> 09:37.645
you might want to go
in a different direction.

09:37.678 --> 09:39.312
Emery: Who better to capture
the real Jessica Huang

09:39.346 --> 09:42.650
than two people who came out
of Jessica Huang?

09:45.518 --> 09:47.287
Jessica:
Oh, these are all blurry.

09:47.320 --> 09:49.456
My hands shake
when I get excited.

09:49.489 --> 09:51.158
These are terrible.

09:51.191 --> 09:53.727
No need to decide right now!
We'll wait to hear from you.

09:53.761 --> 09:55.295
You sleep on it.
Take your time.

09:55.328 --> 09:56.396
**

09:56.429 --> 09:58.165
[ Bell rings ]

09:59.366 --> 10:01.301
How bad
was detention?
Did you
have to make a shiv?

10:01.334 --> 10:02.803
You would know
if you didn't bail on me.

10:02.836 --> 10:06.006
Hey, we apologized
in the moment.

10:06.039 --> 10:08.141
**

10:08.175 --> 10:09.442
Sorry.

10:09.476 --> 10:12.012
Hey. Pretty cool
how you slept through detention

10:12.045 --> 10:13.814
even though the lady coach
said not to.

10:13.847 --> 10:14.815
Thanks.

10:14.848 --> 10:16.583
Not to brag or whatever,
but...

10:16.616 --> 10:18.118
I can
fall asleep anywhere.

10:18.151 --> 10:19.653
You want
to eat lunch with us?

10:19.687 --> 10:23.190
**

10:23.223 --> 10:25.325
Yeah. Cool.

10:25.358 --> 10:26.326
**

10:26.359 --> 10:28.295
See you
good boys later.

10:28.328 --> 10:31.298
**

10:40.240 --> 10:41.374
[ Wind whistling ]

10:41.408 --> 10:45.445
[ Birds chirping,
whimsical music plays ]

10:45.478 --> 10:47.681
Why do I suddenly feel
much happier?

10:47.715 --> 10:50.450
It's 'cause
you're off campus, bro.
This is amazing!

10:50.483 --> 10:52.786
Every day at lunch,
we get tacos at Taco Fiesta.

10:52.820 --> 10:54.621
That means "taco party"
in English.

10:54.654 --> 10:55.956
So, you guys
don't even, like,

10:55.989 --> 10:57.457
care what
the cafeteria's serving!

10:57.490 --> 10:59.359
[ Scoffs ]
What's a cafeteria?

10:59.392 --> 11:02.529
[ Laughs ]
Let's roll.

11:02.562 --> 11:04.965
[ Typewriter keys clacking ]

11:04.998 --> 11:07.167
Okay, I need to get this
off my chest.

11:07.200 --> 11:08.535
Eddie got detention.

11:08.568 --> 11:10.871
I didn't want to tell you
because I know you've been busy,

11:10.904 --> 11:12.472
but it's been eating
at me.

11:12.505 --> 11:13.741
Not now,
I'm in the zone.

11:13.774 --> 11:15.208
Great! [ Chuckles ]

11:15.242 --> 11:17.410
So technically,
we talked about it.

11:17.444 --> 11:19.212
Whew!
I feel so unburdened.

11:19.246 --> 11:20.914
Good parenting,
good partnership.

11:20.948 --> 11:23.383
Okay, so, uh,
I'm a little hungry,

11:23.416 --> 11:25.252
so I'm gonna go microwave
a bean burrito.

11:25.285 --> 11:26.586
It was a two-pack

11:26.619 --> 11:28.388
and somebody made one
and threw out the directions,

11:28.421 --> 11:29.990
so I'm gonna put it in
for 30 seconds at a time

11:30.023 --> 11:31.224
and keep checking it.

11:31.258 --> 11:33.160
Anyway, you're writing.
You're writing, so...

11:33.193 --> 11:34.161
I'm gonna...

11:34.194 --> 11:35.228
[ Door opens ]

11:36.764 --> 11:39.166
Look at you
back at it.
Yes,
I'm in the zone.

11:39.199 --> 11:41.068
I don't want
to disturb you.

11:41.101 --> 11:42.269
Just real quick --

11:42.302 --> 11:44.938
I'm making one last plea
to use this photo.

11:44.972 --> 11:47.074
The one where I caught you
uncapping a pen.

11:47.107 --> 11:48.175
I don't need
a photo anymore.

11:48.208 --> 11:49.777
I'm scrapping that book.
I'm writing a new one.

11:49.810 --> 11:50.944
What?

11:50.978 --> 11:52.379
Yes,
a children's book

11:52.412 --> 11:54.915
about an alligator
who eats dreams.

11:54.948 --> 11:56.616
You're just giving up
on your book?

11:56.649 --> 11:58.051
What about
Vera and Terry?

11:58.085 --> 12:00.020
They'll be fine.
They have each other.

12:00.053 --> 12:02.622
I couldn't sleep last night,
and I realized

12:02.655 --> 12:05.225
the reason I can't pick a photo
for that book

12:05.258 --> 12:07.394
is because that book
is the problem.

12:07.427 --> 12:09.897
This one
is much better.
[ Microwave door opens ]

12:09.930 --> 12:12.632
The boy, Kevin,
wants to be an astronaut,

12:12.665 --> 12:15.202
but then the alligator
eats the moon.

12:15.235 --> 12:17.637
So he's just gonna stay
where he is.

12:17.670 --> 12:19.139
[ Microwave beeping ]

12:20.607 --> 12:22.042
[ Muffled ]
It's so good.

12:22.075 --> 12:24.111
Hot.
It's hot, but so good.

12:24.144 --> 12:26.579
[ Breathing heavily ]

12:26.613 --> 12:27.915
[ Upbeat music playing ]

12:27.948 --> 12:29.817
Yo.
Check this out.

12:30.951 --> 12:33.954
'Scuse me...Paul.

12:33.987 --> 12:35.322
Could I trouble you
for a cup?

12:35.355 --> 12:36.924
I just want
to grab some water.

12:36.957 --> 12:38.425
[ Sighs ]

12:38.458 --> 12:41.094
You're the best.

12:41.128 --> 12:45.799
**

12:50.337 --> 12:53.106
I can totally
see you.

12:53.140 --> 12:54.942
[ Music continues ]

12:54.975 --> 12:57.577
Good thing I don't
get paid enough to care.

12:57.610 --> 12:58.645
[ Sighs ]

12:58.678 --> 13:00.080
**

13:00.113 --> 13:01.915
That's that outlaw life,
yo!

13:01.949 --> 13:03.750
You fools
paid for your sodas.

13:03.783 --> 13:05.986
I can't believe we weren't
sure about you at first.

13:06.019 --> 13:08.922
I mean, we saw you were
friends with that nerd
Safety Patrol kid.

13:08.956 --> 13:10.858
Trent?
He's a real bummer.

13:10.891 --> 13:12.492
He's the one who confiscated
our sacks.

13:12.525 --> 13:14.361
They're locked away
in the principal's office,

13:14.394 --> 13:15.662
never to be
hacked again.

13:15.695 --> 13:18.765
I can probably help you
get your sacks back.

13:18.798 --> 13:20.167
How?

13:20.200 --> 13:21.801
Trent's locker is near
the bathroom I visit

13:21.835 --> 13:22.870
when I need to TCB.

13:24.237 --> 13:25.538
"Take care
of business."

13:25.572 --> 13:27.007
He gave me
the combination

13:27.040 --> 13:28.775
so I can store reading material
in there.

13:28.808 --> 13:30.310
All we got to do
is get in his locker,

13:30.343 --> 13:32.379
get the keys
to the principal's office,

13:32.412 --> 13:33.480
and free the sacks.

13:33.513 --> 13:34.514
Nice.

13:34.547 --> 13:36.449
Okay.
Here's the plan.

13:36.483 --> 13:39.887
Eddie: We wait until
Trent finishes his shift.

13:39.920 --> 13:43.356
Then, we help ourselves
to those keys.

13:43.390 --> 13:46.826
**

13:51.564 --> 13:52.799
I know Principal Mathis

13:52.832 --> 13:54.701
will be out of her office
all afternoon.

13:54.734 --> 13:56.169
She's due in court

13:56.203 --> 13:58.238
to defend the school's
musical production of "Brent."

13:58.271 --> 14:02.409
**

14:06.779 --> 14:07.981
[ Whispering ]
Keep reading.

14:08.015 --> 14:09.549
Come on, Morrie.
Keep it interesting.

14:09.582 --> 14:11.218
**

14:11.251 --> 14:13.586
[ Sighs ]
You guys get your sacks back,

14:13.620 --> 14:18.058
we replace Trent's keys --
in and out.

14:18.091 --> 14:20.693
Eddie,
that was awesome!

14:20.727 --> 14:21.895
You're a total badass.

14:21.929 --> 14:22.930
Yeah, man!

14:22.963 --> 14:24.831
Hey,
here's your cut!

14:24.864 --> 14:26.699
[ Stammers ]
My cut?

14:26.733 --> 14:28.201
We found Mathis' petty cash
sitting on her desk,

14:28.235 --> 14:29.536
so we
helped ourselves.

14:29.569 --> 14:31.571
Yeah, and I also took
these Post-its.

14:31.604 --> 14:32.940
You guys stole money
from the school?

14:32.973 --> 14:34.541
Yeah, man,
and these Post-its.

14:34.574 --> 14:35.909
We couldn't have done it
without you.

14:35.943 --> 14:37.210
Now, who wants some
7-Eleven slushies?

14:37.244 --> 14:39.379
[ Gasps ] Yes!
Slushies!
Oh! Slushies!

14:39.412 --> 14:41.881
Eddie, what's wrong?
You didn't yell, "Slushies."

14:41.915 --> 14:43.250
Oh, sorry.

14:43.283 --> 14:44.551
Slushies!

14:44.584 --> 14:46.286
Yeah, that's what
I'm talking about.

14:46.319 --> 14:48.055
Let's go.

14:51.959 --> 14:52.926
Did you hear
about Trent?

14:52.960 --> 14:53.961
Walter:
His key was used

14:53.994 --> 14:55.095
to break into
the principal's office.

14:55.128 --> 14:56.096
Someone stole $300.

14:56.129 --> 14:57.430
Oh, yeah?

14:57.464 --> 14:59.866
He got kicked off
Safety Patrol -- his one joy.

14:59.899 --> 15:00.934
**

15:00.968 --> 15:02.635
Here he comes.

15:02.669 --> 15:04.537
Hey, bud.

15:04.571 --> 15:06.439
Sorry about
Safety Patrol.

15:06.473 --> 15:07.574
Thanks.

15:07.607 --> 15:09.142
It's not like it's your fault
or anything.

15:09.176 --> 15:11.811
All I ask is that you don't
treat me with kid gloves.

15:11.844 --> 15:14.547
Oh.
You're wearing sneakers.

15:14.581 --> 15:15.648
That's great.

15:15.682 --> 15:17.985
I'm glad
your feet are safe.

15:18.018 --> 15:21.788
**

15:21.821 --> 15:23.123
[ Typewriter keys clacking ]

15:23.156 --> 15:26.559
"'Sorry, little Linda,'
said the alligator,

15:26.593 --> 15:30.230
'You can't become a doctor
because I ate the hospital.'"

15:30.263 --> 15:31.798
Evan:
[ Clears throat ]

15:31.831 --> 15:33.766
Honey informed us you're writing
a children's book.

15:33.800 --> 15:35.302
If you haven't picked
an illustrator,

15:35.335 --> 15:36.936
we'd like
to toss our hats in the ring.

15:36.970 --> 15:38.938
Leave your portfolio.
I'll take a look.

15:38.972 --> 15:41.341
I hope
there's new stuff in there.

15:41.374 --> 15:42.976
**

15:43.010 --> 15:45.445
We'll circle back.

15:45.478 --> 15:47.180
She's seen these!

15:47.214 --> 15:48.781
I told you
we weren't ready!

15:48.815 --> 15:49.782
[ Sighs ]

15:49.816 --> 15:52.352
[ Telephone rings ]
[ Sighs ]

15:52.385 --> 15:53.653
Hello?

15:53.686 --> 15:55.522
Hi, Vera...

15:55.555 --> 15:57.190
or Terry.

15:57.224 --> 15:58.691
I'm glad you called.

15:58.725 --> 16:00.760
I have news.

16:00.793 --> 16:02.062
What?

16:04.131 --> 16:06.033
Betrayal!
Sorry?

16:06.066 --> 16:07.434
Vera or Terry
just called.

16:07.467 --> 16:09.202
They said
they loved my author photo!

16:09.236 --> 16:11.538
How could you send them
a picture I didn't approve?

16:11.571 --> 16:13.440
Because the picture
doesn't matter.

16:13.473 --> 16:16.376
And you were so worried
about it, you were gonna
throw away your whole book.

16:16.409 --> 16:19.346
None of those photos make me
look like I'm a real author.

16:19.379 --> 16:21.481
But you are
a real author.

16:22.515 --> 16:25.552
Ohh,
what is happening?

16:25.585 --> 16:26.953
I feel like...

16:26.986 --> 16:30.290
all of my power
is draining from me.

16:30.323 --> 16:34.661
I think maybe
you're experiencing insecurity.

16:34.694 --> 16:36.329
No, that's dumb.

16:36.363 --> 16:38.165
Why else would you
be sabotaging this?

16:38.198 --> 16:40.800
You're the alligator
eating your own dream.

16:40.833 --> 16:43.703
What if
nobody buys my book?

16:43.736 --> 16:46.306
Well, you can't
control that.

16:46.339 --> 16:48.341
I really want
to control it.

16:48.375 --> 16:49.342
You wrote a book,

16:49.376 --> 16:51.044
and you're
getting it published.

16:51.078 --> 16:52.412
That's a very big deal.

16:52.445 --> 16:53.513
I know it is,

16:53.546 --> 16:55.415
and then if I fail,
everyone's gonna know.

16:55.448 --> 16:58.351
Yeah, but if you fail,
then you'll have failed

16:58.385 --> 17:01.754
at something that most people
are afraid of even trying.

17:02.789 --> 17:04.691
You're saying
even if I fail,

17:04.724 --> 17:06.393
people will still
be jealous of me?

17:06.426 --> 17:07.760
Sure.

17:07.794 --> 17:11.198
Besides, you know one person
who's gonna buy your book --

17:11.231 --> 17:12.399
Me.

17:12.432 --> 17:13.866
Thank you, Honey.

17:13.900 --> 17:15.568
You're a good friend.

17:15.602 --> 17:16.836
In my next book,

17:16.869 --> 17:19.839
I'll name the murder victim
after you.

17:19.872 --> 17:21.741
Yay!

17:21.774 --> 17:23.443
You're welcome.

17:23.476 --> 17:24.944
Louis:
Strongly agree.

17:24.977 --> 17:26.879
Strongly agree.

17:26.913 --> 17:28.681
[ Door opens ]

17:28.715 --> 17:30.117
Agree.

17:30.150 --> 17:31.951
Moderately disagree.

17:31.984 --> 17:34.554
I got to go.
Goodbye, Mom.

17:34.587 --> 17:37.624
Don't tell me
you got detention again.

17:37.657 --> 17:39.759
No.
I need some advice.

17:39.792 --> 17:41.728
Say you run
a dishwasher,

17:41.761 --> 17:43.730
but it's
a really big dishwasher.

17:43.763 --> 17:45.098
You ran
the dishwasher again?

17:45.132 --> 17:46.899
Honestly,
I'm more impressed than angry.

17:46.933 --> 17:47.934
How did you reconnect --

17:47.967 --> 17:50.270
No. Sorry.
Let me try this again.

17:50.303 --> 17:53.373
Say you wear
some slides to school,

17:53.406 --> 17:55.142
but they fall off
and kill a man.

17:55.175 --> 17:57.210
Eddie, metaphors are not
your strong suit.

17:57.244 --> 17:59.045
I get the sense that
you don't want me to ask you

17:59.078 --> 18:00.947
what's going on,
but what is going on?

18:00.980 --> 18:03.883
I accidentally helped
some older kids steal
money from the school.

18:03.916 --> 18:05.285
What?!

18:05.318 --> 18:07.254
And Trent got blamed for it,
and now he's off safety patrol.

18:08.521 --> 18:10.157
Do you think
I'm a bad person?

18:10.190 --> 18:11.158
[ Chuckles ]

18:11.191 --> 18:12.892
A bad person
wouldn't be upset

18:12.925 --> 18:14.494
about letting his friend
take the fall.

18:14.527 --> 18:16.263
You just
made a mistake.

18:16.296 --> 18:18.331
I know you'll figure out a way
to make it a right.

18:18.365 --> 18:20.600
I do know
how to make this right,

18:20.633 --> 18:22.602
but I'm gonna need
your help.

18:22.635 --> 18:27.140
**

18:34.947 --> 18:37.083
I don't want you
to see me like this.

18:37.116 --> 18:38.084
Wait.

18:38.117 --> 18:39.786
I have information
you can use

18:39.819 --> 18:41.421
to get back
on Safety Patrol.

18:41.454 --> 18:45.192
[ Indistinct conversation ]

18:45.225 --> 18:48.528
Sorry, boys,
no off-campus tacos for you.

18:48.561 --> 18:50.697
Looks like you'll be having
cheese soup

18:50.730 --> 18:51.964
with the rest
of the school.

18:51.998 --> 18:53.433
Good work,
Trent.

18:53.466 --> 18:55.668
Let's get you back
in that orange vest

18:55.702 --> 18:57.204
where you belong,
hmm?

18:57.237 --> 18:59.472
I hear it looks great
from the back.

19:03.042 --> 19:06.546
Only $350 left to go
till your debt is paid.

19:06.579 --> 19:07.714
But I only
borrowed $300!

19:07.747 --> 19:09.015
At a very high
interest rate.

19:09.048 --> 19:11.184
Bank of Louis.
Should've shopped around.

19:11.218 --> 19:14.187
I know you don't
want to hear this, but...

19:14.221 --> 19:15.955
you're not a bad boy.

19:15.988 --> 19:17.123
[ Both chuckle ]

19:17.156 --> 19:20.126
[ Sighs ] Brutal.

19:20.159 --> 19:21.528
I guess it's true.

19:21.561 --> 19:24.297
Asian dads don't say,
"I love you."

19:24.331 --> 19:25.798
**

19:25.832 --> 19:27.700
So, the photo Honey sent in
was yours?

19:27.734 --> 19:29.436
Yes.
She knew she was bested.

19:31.738 --> 19:35.708
[ Dramatic music plays ]

19:35.742 --> 19:37.477
I love it.
You do?

19:37.510 --> 19:38.578
Yes.

19:38.611 --> 19:41.581
It's challenging people
to not like my book.

19:42.882 --> 19:45.318
"What?
You don't like it?

19:45.352 --> 19:47.720
What,
you got a problem?

19:47.754 --> 19:49.889
Yeah,
I'm talking to you.

19:49.922 --> 19:52.024
Let's see you write
an entire novel.

19:52.058 --> 19:53.092
That's right!

19:53.125 --> 19:57.096
Run away
to cookbooks, coward."

19:57.129 --> 19:58.865
**

19:58.898 --> 20:00.600
[ Sighs ]

20:00.633 --> 20:03.770
[ Chatter ]

20:07.274 --> 20:09.542
We thought you ditched us
to hangout with the Sackers.

20:09.576 --> 20:11.378
Sorry, guys.
That was stupid of me.

20:11.411 --> 20:14.581
Turns out the Sackers are not
cooler than the dip kids.

20:18.117 --> 20:20.387
[ Rock music playing ]

20:20.420 --> 20:22.922
* We're not gonna pay

20:22.955 --> 20:25.692
* We're not gonna pay

20:25.725 --> 20:28.060
* We're not gonna pay

20:28.094 --> 20:30.763
* This guy Brent

20:30.797 --> 20:33.566
* That guy Brent

20:33.600 --> 20:35.201
What is this
about anyway?

20:35.234 --> 20:37.604
I-I don't know,
but a lot of them have the flu.

20:37.637 --> 20:39.038
[ Sneezes ]
[ Sniffles ]

20:39.071 --> 20:41.541
* We're not gonna pay Brent

20:41.574 --> 20:43.510
* Brent, Brent,
Brent, Brent, Brent *

20:47.580 --> 20:50.717
[ "Seasons of Love" plays ]

20:50.750 --> 20:55.888
* 315,557,000

20:55.922 --> 20:58.558
* Seconds a year

20:58.591 --> 21:01.394
* It's time now for flu shots

21:01.428 --> 21:03.563
* Our immune systems win

21:03.596 --> 21:05.332
* Let's wash our hands
I am onboard.

21:05.365 --> 21:07.600
I wasn't at first, but I am now.

21:07.634 --> 21:09.936
* We'll make it through

21:09.969 --> 21:11.504
Shut it down!
[ Chatter ]

21:11.538 --> 21:13.506
We lost the case!
No more singing!

21:13.540 --> 21:15.107
Give me those programs.

21:15.141 --> 21:16.576
We have to shred them.

21:16.609 --> 21:19.812
Turns out we are in fact
in violation of copyright,

21:19.846 --> 21:21.614
so live and learn,
I guess.

21:21.648 --> 21:23.115
Pass them.

21:23.149 --> 21:25.117
Pass them down.

21:25.151 --> 21:26.319
Pass them down!
